Paulina Juhnke

The earliest record for Paulina Juhnke is the 1870 census, where she was living with her parents in Newton, Marquette County, Wisconsin (1). By the 1880 census, Paulina had married Frank Collins, and the two lived with her parents in Newton, Marquette County, Wisconsin (2). By the 1900 census, the two had moved out of Paulina’s parent’s house and made a home at 8 Fulton Street, Edgerton, Rock County, Wisconsin (3).

By the 1910 census, Paulina and Frank’s family had moved to Rockford where they are recorded as living at North First Street, Rockford, Illinois (4) and in the 1920 census, Paulina and Frank are recorded as living at Pearl Avenue, Rockford, Illinois with their son George(5).

According to the 1930 census, Paulina and Frank Collins lived alone at 88 Long Island, Rockford, Illinois (6). A year later, Paulina died at the age of 71 on the 4th of April, 1931 (7).
